# Inkwave environment variables. Copy to `.env` for local dev (optional — defaults work), and set
# in Vercel for production. VITE_* are PUBLIC (baked into the client bundle); the rest are
# server-only (read by the /api functions) and must never be exposed to the client.

# ─── Server-only (Vercel env, never in the client) ───────────────────────────
# Ed25519 secret key (hex) the signing service signs receipts with.
INKWAVE_SIGNING_SK=
# Master secret for deriving per-document exclusion sets S_v.
INKWAVE_MASTER_SECRET=

# ─── Public (VITE_*, safe in the client) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Override the published signing public key the app verifies against (optional; the committed
# PUBLISHED_SIGNING_PK in src/provenance/receipts.ts is authoritative in production).
VITE_SIGNING_PK=
# Azure app (SPA) client id for OneDrive sync via Microsoft Graph. Without it the "Sync to
# OneDrive" option is hidden. Register a Single-page application in the Microsoft Entra portal,
# add redirect URIs (https://inkwave.studio + http://localhost:5173), and grant the delegated
# Microsoft Graph permission Files.ReadWrite.AppFolder (+ User.Read).
VITE_MS_CLIENT_ID=
